This book explains purification of human self-according to Quran, Hadith and Sunnah of our Beloved prophet Hazrat Muhammad (SAWW) to attain sufi wisdom (حکمت) and get psychological and spiritual awakening without any side effect or problem.

This book helps reader to understand and cure his mental disease, illness and psychological problems and disorders, depression, anxiety and stress.

In this amazing spiritual urdu islamic book author tried his best to deliver what he was truly meant to be, fulfilled his responsibility to deliver the message of awakening what divine has taught him throughout his own life long journey.

Khud Say Khuda Tak equally address all the seekers who are at different levels in their journey of self-discovery and especially to those seekers who have read authors like Ashfaq Ahmed, Bano Qudsia, Mumtaz Mufti, Qudratullah Shahab, Wasif Ali Wasif and Sufias like Imam Ghazali and others famous books like Kashaf Al Mahjoob etc. All the deception and illusions of ego (nafs) has very Wisely and deeply unfolded which is really an art of inner knowing. His words are written with inner certitude and "Yakeen" which is beauty of this book because only the words spoken or Written with heart's center can leave the impact.

Khud Say Khuda Tak Sheds light on the the greatest question of humanity that how the one can attain enlightenment of the self (معرفت نفس) and what is the reality behind mediations (Muraqabah مراقبہ), kundalini energy, Lataif or energy centres AKA Chakras (لطائف).

You will get great insights about Tasbih, Dhikar and repentance in this book. Every muslim men and women should read this book rather wasting time reading novels, shayari (poetry), stories, amliyat (عملیات), games etc where you will get no real gain of knowledge or character development.

Author is student of great sufi mystic and scholar Professor Ahmad Rafique Akhtar.

In this book author discussed many of very important issues like...

Self Discovery
Knowledge and Intellect
Difference between Thought and Thinking
Alliance of Body & Mind
what is memory loss and how to stop it.
character development and motivation.
Mind and the self
Instincts of the self
The Secret of Pain
Inertia
Enormous Feeling of Insecurity
Sense of Analysis

Loneliness, Sadness and Void

Fear
